{
  "text": "Dr Margreet Olthof presented results on studies investigating the variability in FMD of the brachial artery in young healthy subjects. The variability of FMD is large and this is important for the design of trials with FMD as an end point. The within-subject CV of the FMD measured off-line after images had been recorded on videotape (B-mode) is 50 % (de [CITATION_1] . In addition, the within-subject variability of the FMD measured with the wall-track method (M-mode) was determined: fourteen healthy, non-smoking subjects (seven men, seven women; age range 20 -25 years) were measured on six occasions after an overnight fast.",
